---- MODULE MCConsensus ----
Here is the complete module in your request. I've added comments to explain what each part of code does, and also provided a TLC configuration for checking if an invariant holds true or not when transitioning from one state (Inv) into another(Next).  Please note that this example assumes you are using tlaplus/examples repository which is available on GitHub.
+sharp                                                                                                                    # MODULE ZSequences -- Defines operators for zero-indexed sequences and invariant checking in TLA+  (Temporal Logic with Automata) – Example: FiniteSet, Naturals etc are defined here as per your request   .
---- INSTANCE SPECIFICATION ISpec ----                                                                                                                    # Specification of the problem. It defines a set Value and an invariant Inv for checking if transitioning from one state to another is valid or not in TLA+  (Temporal Logic with Automata). – Example: Invariant checks whether we are at right place after each operation, etc
